terms.medium_def:
A man of the Arabs living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.15; 
only referred to as Naphish (נָפִישׁ); 
son of Ishmael; 
a brother of Nebaioth, Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Kedemah and Mahalath.

People from Naphtuh(?) of the Egyptians, first mentioned at Gen.10.13; 
only referred to as Naphtuhim (נַפְתֻּחִים); 
descended from Egypt along with Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Pathrusim, Casluhim and Caphtorim. § an unclear reference to Egypt; perhaps Lower Egypt
